DCM summary results

Aniol Santo Angles

November 2022

Manuscript figures with PEB results were created with the present summary of results. Here, PEB results are presented in matrix form (rows as target region, columns as source region). Colored squares in matrix signal those connections with posterior probability Pp > 0.85. Red (blue) square means condition 1 higher (lower) than condition 2 (e.g., delay vs baseline, or correct vs swap). Quantitative information about PEB is presented in table with the following columns: Parameter (in column form described above), Ep (PEB parameter), Pp (posterior probability). Brain regions: SFG, superior frontal gyrus; cMFG, contralateral middle frontal gyrus; iMFG ipsilateral middle frontal gyrus; cLIP, contralateral lateral intraparietal; iLIP, ipsilateral lateral intraparietal; cEVC, contralateral early visual cortex; iEVC ipsilateral early visual cortex. Contralateral (ipsilateral) relative to stimulus presentation.
